      "writtenOn": "2020-08-26T19:40:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Note this is a pragmatic decision to be cw. Skia is y-down and positive angles are visually clockwise (at least that\u0027s how sweep angles seem to be defined). OpenType is y-up and negative angles are visual clockwise. Taking and reporting this consistent with the rest of Skia allows for a direct answer to the question, \"If I want to draw an angle to match what do I pass in to Skia?\". However, it does mean that this will have the opposite sign of a typical \u0027ital\u0027 variation value since that will be specified in OpenType units. I think this will end up ok, since this is how CSS works (positive angles visually clockwise, but \u0027ital\u0027 axis values will need to be negated from that).",
